Key Match Events: Immanuel Quickley made a 29-foot three-pointer to cap a 25-6 Raptors run in the fourth quarter.
Pre-Game Insights: Quickley had been out for 22 games due to injury and was grateful to be back on the court.
Post-Match Reflections: Scottie Barnes led all scorers with 33 points and 13 rebounds.
Head coach Darko Rajakovic praised Quickley's impact on the offense and his ability to call plays on the run.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The Raptors snapped an 11-game losing skid.
Quickley averaged 18.6 points, 6.8 assists, and 4.8 rebounds in 38 games last season.
